Package: alfak2
Title: ALFA-K2: Adaptive Local-to-Global Fitness Landscapes for Aneuploid Karyotypes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Richard", family = "Beck",
           email = "richard.beck@moffitt.org", role = "aut"),
    person(given = "Tao", family = "Li",
           email = "Tao.Li2@moffitt.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Author: Richard Beck [aut], Tao Li [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Tao Li <Tao.Li2@moffitt.org>
Description: ALFA-K2 (Adaptive Local-to-Global Fitness Landscapes for Aneuploid
    Karyotypes) provides methods to infer fitness landscapes for aneuploid karyotypes from
    sparse two-timepoint count data and use those landscapes to study karyotype
    evolution. The package builds bounded karyotype graphs, fits a local
    hierarchical Bayesian model, and propagates estimates across the graph with
    a Gaussian-process prior and ordered copy-number epistasis penalties.
